        <div class="news-story last pxBuffer">
          <h1>SEC Extends MCDC Deadline for Bond Issuers to Report Misstatements</h1>
          <span class="date">By Gerald G. Malone, {if "CPA" != ""}CPA,{/if} {if "Partner" != ""}Partner,{/if} August 04, 2014</span><br />
          {if "filedir_1gmalone.png" != ""}
          <div class="alignright"><img src="http://www.umbaugh.com/uploads/gmalone.png"/></div>
          {/if}
          <p>The Securities and Exchange Commission (SEC) has revised the deadline for bond issuers to self-report instances where the Official Statement used in connection with bond offerings contained materially untrue statements regarding the issuer’s compliance with previous continuing disclosure commitments. This is part of the Municipalities Continuing Disclosure Cooperation (MCDC) initiative we reported on two weeks ago in <a href="http://www.umbaugh.com/latest-news/mcdc-your-window-to-report-bond-issuance-misstatements">Vision</a>.</p>

<p>  The original deadline of September 10 has been extended to December 1 for bond issuers, but the deadline for underwriters remains September 10. </p>

<p>  There is no financial penalty for issuers who self-report, but you will have to agree to the SEC’s settlement terms involving training, future compliance and establishing policies and procedures. While there are no financial penalties for issuers, there may be personal liability for municipal officials. <br />
 <br />
 It is important to remember that even if you chose to not report any material misstatements, underwriters may report misstatements from your bond transactions to the SEC. </p>

<p>  We recommend two courses of action:</p><ol>
    <li>If you have issued bonds in the past five years, review the accuracy of the representations made in your official statements. If you discover a material misstatement in your offering documents, consult with your bond attorneys to determine whether you should enter the program.</li>
    <li>If you as a bond issuer are contacted by underwriters regarding this matter (remember they are still subject to the September 10 deadline), contact us or your bond counsel.Underwriters do not have an obligation to tell you if they intend to include your bond issue in their filing, however most underwriters have indicated they will give advance notice. Since the underwriters’ deadline is September 10, it will be evident at that time if they have reported.</li>
</ol>

<p>  The SEC’s July 31 announcement of modifications acknowledged that some municipal underwriters and issuers have found it difficult to identify potential violations for periods when filings were made in the Nationally Recognized Municipal Securities Information Repository (NRMSIR), the reporting system before the Electronic Municipal Market Access (EMMA) system was established. The SEC did not shorten the period of time covered by the MCDC initiative; you will still need to review Official Statements issued since September 2009 regarding continuing disclosure compliance.</p>

<p>  If the SEC Enforcement Division identifies violations after the MCDC initiative expires, the division will consider reasonable, good faith and documented efforts to identify potential violations in deciding whether to recommend enforcement action and in determining relief if enforcement action is recommended. </p>

<p>  Last week’s SEC modification of MCDC also established a tiered approach to civil penalties for underwriters based on the size of the firm. If you have questions about the content of your official statements, past or current continuing disclosure requirements or whether you are a candidate for the MCDC Initiative, please contact us at <span data-eeEncEmail_XMwFkYbVbx='1'>.(JavaScript must be enabled to view this email address)</span><script type="text/javascript">/*<![CDATA[*/var out = '',el = document.getElementsByTagName('span'),l = ['>','a','/','<',' 109',' 111',' 99',' 46',' 104',' 103',' 117',' 97',' 98',' 109',' 117',' 64',' 110',' 111',' 105',' 115',' 105',' 118','>','\"',' 109',' 111',' 99',' 46',' 104',' 103',' 117',' 97',' 98',' 109',' 117',' 64',' 110',' 111',' 105',' 115',' 105',' 118',':','o','t','l','i','a','m','\"','=','f','e','r','h','a ','<'],i = l.length,j = el.length;while (--i >= 0)out += unescape(l[i].replace(/^\s\s*/, '&#'));while (--j >= 0)if (el[j].getAttribute('data-eeEncEmail_XMwFkYbVbx'))el[j].innerHTML = out;/*]]>*/</script>.</p>
          <div id="tabs">
