        <div class="news-story last pxBuffer">
          <h1>Debt Service Cash Reserves Are Reduced Under New Law</h1>
          <span class="date">By Paige E. Sansone, {if "CPA" != ""}CPA,{/if} {if "Principal" != ""}Principal,{/if} July 30, 2014</span><br />
          {if "filedir_1pgregory.png" != ""}
          <div class="alignright"><img src="http://www.umbaugh.com/uploads/pgregory.png"/></div>
          {/if}
          <p>Prior to the passage of HEA1062 in the 2014 Indiana General Assembly session, taxing units could levy property tax sufficient to fund two debt payments in the current budget year plus the first debt payment in the following year. In other words, the ending cash balance for debt service funds could be enough to make a debt payment in the following year before receiving the spring property tax settlement. </p>

<p>  Beginning with the 2015 budgets, HEA 1062 changes the maximum cash reserve for debt service funds. Debt originally incurred before July 1, 2014 will have a maximum debt service cash reserve limit of 50% of the budget estimate for total annual debt payments. In most cases, this reserve level should be sufficient to fund (or at least come close to) the first debt payment in the following year. </p>

<p>  Debt issued after June 30, 2014 will have a maximum cash reserve limit of 15% of the budget estimate for total annual debt payments. In this case, the level of cash reserves is not likely to cover the first debt payment in the following year. If you face a cash flow shortage from the 15% limit, you may borrow from another fund temporarily to make the debt payment. If there is not enough cash to borrow from other funds, you may need a temporary loan from a financial institution. That process could take 30 days or more, so you will need to plan ahead. External borrowing should be viewed as a last resort. </p>

<p>  If you have questions or need assistance with budgeting or financial planning, please contact us at <span data-eeEncEmail_ckMuRoznQv='1'>.(JavaScript must be enabled to view this email address)</span><script type="text/javascript">/*<![CDATA[*/var out = '',el = document.getElementsByTagName('span'),l = ['>','a','/','<',' 109',' 111',' 99',' 46',' 104',' 103',' 117',' 97',' 98',' 109',' 117',' 64',' 110',' 111',' 105',' 115',' 105',' 118','>','\"',' 109',' 111',' 99',' 46',' 104',' 103',' 117',' 97',' 98',' 109',' 117',' 64',' 110',' 111',' 105',' 115',' 105',' 118',':','o','t','l','i','a','m','\"','=','f','e','r','h','a ','<'],i = l.length,j = el.length;while (--i >= 0)out += unescape(l[i].replace(/^\s\s*/, '&#'));while (--j >= 0)if (el[j].getAttribute('data-eeEncEmail_ckMuRoznQv'))el[j].innerHTML = out;/*]]>*/</script>.</p>
