          <h1>Tyler K. Blake Earns Promotion to Manager</h1>
          <span class="date">By Umbaugh Announcements, {if "" != ""},{/if} {if "" != ""},{/if} July 30, 2014</span><br />
          {if "filedir_1TylerBlake_68R0233.png" != ""}
          <div class="alignright"><img src="http://www.umbaugh.com/uploads/TylerBlake_68R0233.png"/></div>
          {/if}
          <p>Please join us in congratulating Tyler K. Blake, CPA, who was promoted to a client manager at Umbaugh July 1st. Tyler works on a wide range of engagements, with a focus on cities, towns and utility matters. </p>

<p>  He is based in our Indianapolis office and is a graduate of the Indiana University-Bloomington Kelley School of Business where he earned a double major in accounting and finance. Upon graduation in 2008, he began working for a public accounting firm based in New Albany, Indiana. </p>

<p>  Tyler joined Umbaugh in 2012 and says he has enjoyed getting to know our clients: “I enjoy meeting with local officials, hearing about their projects and working to find solutions that help their community.” </p>

<p>  He is a member of American Institute of CPAs (AICPA), the Indiana CPA Society and the Indiana Water Environment Association. </p>

