        <div class="news-story last pxBuffer">
          <h1>2014 Legislative Session: New Impact, Options and Unintended Consequences</h1>
          <span class="date">By Umbaugh Announcements, {if "" != ""},{/if} {if "" != ""},{/if} April 08, 2014</span><br />
          {if "" != ""}
          <div class="alignright"><img src=""/></div>
          {/if}
          <p>A number of bills intended to benefit Indiana taxpayers and communities could create new fiscal impacts on Indiana schools, counties, cities and towns. In some cases, those bills also have unintended consequences. The bills listed below are particularly pertinent to local governments, redevelopment commissions, utilities and schools:</p><ul>
    <li><b>SEA 1</b> provides new options to Indiana counties for reducing business personal property taxes.</li>
    <li><b>SEA 118</b> impacts redevelopment commissions and TIF and generally increases oversight and control by the legislative body.</li>
    <li><b>HEA 1062</b> provides limited relief to certain eligible school corporations regarding protected taxes and debt restructuring. HEA 1062 also limits the debt service fund operating balance, which will affect all property tax debt issuers.</li>
    <li><b>HEA 1187</b> deals with settling sewer and water territorial disputes outside municipal boundaries.</li>
    <li><b>HB 273</b> would have impacted the annexation process and placed a moratorium on involuntary annexations. This bill did not pass.</li>
</ul>

<p>  Look for upcoming articles in Umbaugh Footnotes that will delve into these bills and potential impacts and considerations. See the <a href="http://www.umbaugh.com/senate-bill-1-a-compromise-with-options">article on SEA 1</a> included in this issue.</p>

<p>  It takes some time after every legislative session to understand the fiscal impact of the final version of various bills. Some communities or districts will experience greater fiscal impact because of their unique circumstances. We look forward to helping you understand and analyze potential impacts on your community.</p>

<p>  If any new legislation is of immediate concern to you, please contact us at <span data-eeEncEmail_rjOrwlfgJd='1'>.(JavaScript must be enabled to view this email address)</span><script type="text/javascript">/*<![CDATA[*/var out = '',el = document.getElementsByTagName('span'),l = ['>','a','/','<',' 109',' 111',' 99',' 46',' 104',' 103',' 117',' 97',' 98',' 109',' 117',' 64',' 110',' 111',' 105',' 115',' 105',' 118','>','\"',' 109',' 111',' 99',' 46',' 104',' 103',' 117',' 97',' 98',' 109',' 117',' 64',' 110',' 111',' 105',' 115',' 105',' 118',':','o','t','l','i','a','m','\"','=','f','e','r','h','a ','<'],i = l.length,j = el.length;while (--i >= 0)out += unescape(l[i].replace(/^\s\s*/, '&#'));while (--j >= 0)if (el[j].getAttribute('data-eeEncEmail_rjOrwlfgJd'))el[j].innerHTML = out;/*]]>*/</script>. We’ll be happy to address your questions at any time.</p>
