        <div class="news-story last pxBuffer">
          <h1>Bond Market Still Favorable for Refinancings</h1>
          <span class="date">By Doug Baldessari, {if "CPA" != ""}CPA,{/if} {if "Partner" != ""}Partner,{/if} March 05, 2014</span><br />
          {if "filedir_1dbaldessari.png" != ""}
          <div class="alignright"><img src="http://www.umbaugh.com/uploads/dbaldessari.png"/></div>
          {/if}
          <p>Municipal tax-exempt bond interest rates are no longer at the historic lows we saw in the summer of 2013, but they are still favorable for financing projects or refinancing long-term debt for savings. Municipal bonds which have been outstanding eight or more years are likely able to be refunded for savings — or will be in the near future. </p>

<p> Bond interest rates have been trending down since the first of the year. Average bond interest rates for 20-year AAA-rated issues are currently hovering around 3.5%, and a shorter term issue is even less.</p>

<p> How long will these low interest rates last? No one knows, but many experts believe long-term interest rates will trend up as the Fed scales back on its quantitative easing program. </p>

<p> Your city, town or utility may still achieve interest rate savings by refinancing outstanding bonds or issuing long-term bonds for capital projects to take advantage of the current interest rate market.</p>

<p> <i>If you have questions or would like help to evaluate refinancing opportunities for your outstanding debt, please contact us at <span data-eeEncEmail_lIFYybnwcK='1'>.(JavaScript must be enabled to view this email address)</span><script type="text/javascript">/*<![CDATA[*/var out = '',el = document.getElementsByTagName('span'),l = ['>','a','/','<',' 109',' 111',' 99',' 46',' 104',' 103',' 117',' 97',' 98',' 109',' 117',' 64',' 110',' 111',' 105',' 115',' 105',' 118','>','\"',' 109',' 111',' 99',' 46',' 104',' 103',' 117',' 97',' 98',' 109',' 117',' 64',' 110',' 111',' 105',' 115',' 105',' 118',':','o','t','l','i','a','m','\"','=','f','e','r','h','a ','<'],i = l.length,j = el.length;while (--i >= 0)out += unescape(l[i].replace(/^\s\s*/, '&#'));while (--j >= 0)if (el[j].getAttribute('data-eeEncEmail_lIFYybnwcK'))el[j].innerHTML = out;/*]]>*/</script>.</i></p>
