        <div class="news-story last pxBuffer">
          <h1>Upcoming Deadlines</h1>
          <span class="date">By Paige E. Sansone, {if "CPA" != ""}CPA,{/if} {if "Principal" != ""}Principal,{/if} January 01, 2014</span><br />
          {if "filedir_1pgregory.png" != ""}
          <div class="alignright"><img src="http://www.umbaugh.com/uploads/pgregory.png"/></div>
          {/if}
          <p>As the New Year begins, it is time to focus on wrapping up the previous year. At the close of December, all records must be posted and reconciled with bank statements as promptly as possible. Utilities and other departments maintaining separate records must also be reconciled. Below are upcoming deadlines prescribed by the State Board of Accounts for the first Quarter of the year. Please note that this is not a comprehensive list; you should check the State Board of Accounts Accounting and Compliance Guidelines Manuals for more information.</p>

<p><b>January 31</b> is the last day to furnish each employee with a Form W-2 showing compensation paid during the preceding year, federal tax withheld and Social Security tax withheld. </p>

<p><b>January 31*</b> is the last day to file the Form 100-R (Report of Names, Addresses, Duties and Compensation of Public Employees) with the State Board of Accounts. This form must be filed electronically through Gateway. </p>

<p><b>January 31</b> is the last day to file Other Post Employment Benefits (&#8220;OPEB&#8221;) through Gateway. This applies to all political subdivisions including those that do not offer OPEB. </p>

<p><b>February 18 </b>is the last day for Townships to publish the Annual Financial Report.<b> </b></p>

<p><b>February 28*</b> is the last day to complete an annual review and verify accuracy of debt information in Gateway Debt Management.<b> </b></p>

<p> <b>February 28</b> is the last day to file withholding statements W-2 and WH-2 together with Yearly Reconcilement of Employer&#8217;s Quarterly Tax Returns W-3 and WH-3 with District Director of Internal Revenue and Indiana Department of Revenue, respectively. </p>

<p><b>March 1*</b> is the last day to file the Gateway Annual Financial Report. </p>

<p><b>March 1</b> is the last day to publish the Annual Financial Report for all local units except Townships. </p>

<p><b>March 1</b> is the last day to prepare a list of checks for cancellation that have been outstanding and unpaid for two years. </p>

<p><b>March 1</b> is the last day to file Video Franchise Fee Report with IURC. </p>

<p><b>March 15</b> is the last day for the Redevelopment Commission to submit annual reporting requirements through Gateway. </p>

<p><b>April 1 </b>is the last day to file Water Utility Resource Report with IURC. This applies to all municipal utilities, not just those regulated by the IURC. </p>

<p><b>April 30 </b>is the last day to file the Annual Utility Report with the IURC. This applies to regulated municipal utilities only. * Failure to file one or more of the following reports may result in denial of your budget by the DLGF: 100-R, Annual Financial Report, and Debt Management Report.</p>

